{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595042"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15330"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15330"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8021"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67137"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8021","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8021"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15330"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52593"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19490"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19495"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22464"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67137"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA liver biopsy specimen shows the following features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERegenerative nodules of hepatocytes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDense bands of collagen surrounding the nodules\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBridging fibrosis connecting portal tracts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELoss of normal lobular architecture\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDistorted sinusoidal spaces\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological diagnoses is most likely?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acute hepatitis","Cirrhosis","Focal nodular hyperplasia","Hepatic adenoma","Steatosis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features described are classic for \u003Cstrong\u003Ecirrhosis\u003C/strong\u003E. The key diagnostic features include regenerative nodules surrounded by fibrous septa, with bridging fibrosis disrupting the normal liver architecture. These changes represent the end result of chronic liver injury.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteatosis\u003C/strong\u003E shows accumulation of fat droplets within hepatocytes but does not show fibrosis or nodule formation. \u003Cstrong\u003EAcute hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates inflammatory infiltrates and hepatocyte necrosis without significant fibrosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EFocal nodular hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E shows a central stellate scar with radiating fibrous septa but maintains normal hepatic architecture. \u003Cstrong\u003EHepatic adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E appears as a well-circumscribed mass of hepatocytes without fibrosis or architectural distortion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cirrhosis is characterised by regenerative nodules surrounded by fibrous septa on liver histology","Portal-to-portal and portal-to-central bridging fibrosis are key features of cirrhosis","Disruption of normal liver architecture leads to impaired hepatic function in cirrhosis"],"references":["Sharma B, John S. Hepatic Cirrhosis. [Updated 2022 Oct 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482419/","Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52593"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15330"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52593","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52593"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T16:25:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T16:25:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8021"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67137"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":nu